Pad Thai
via the Chiang Mai Thai Farm Cooking School

200g big, fresh noodles (or 80g of dry noodles, soaked in hot water for 30+ minutes)
1 tsp dark, sweet soy sauce (or dark soy sauce with sugar)(possibly molasses)

1 1/2 tbsp soybean oil
100g sliced tofu

2 cloves garlic, chopped
1/3 cup sliced long beans
1/4 cup sliced carrot (or broccoli)

1 egg, beaten

1 tsp fish sauce (or soy sauce)
1 1/2 tsp sugar

1 spring onion, chopped

Mix dark, sweet soy sauce with bug fresh noodles and set aside.

Heat the oil in the wok.  Fry tofu until golden brown.

Add garlic, long beans, and carrot.  Stir fry until fragrant.

Push the vegetables to one side of the wok and add the beaten egg.  Once they begin to set, quickly scramble them and stir through the vegetables.

Add noodles and season with fish sauce and sugar.  Add spring onion, and stir fry thoroughly until well mixed.
